{
  "texts": [
    "Apropos, an AI researcher Min Choi decided to give it an interesting test, the translation of the Phaistos Disc [32].",
    "As he described in his own words, the translation has no scientific confirmation and is probably wrong.",
    "Nevertheless, he has outlined the whole process he followed on his page on X (formerly twitter) and the scientific hypothesis of using an LLM to do a translation of ancient texts written in an unknown language, is outstandingly impressive.However, do LLMs understand anything from what we give them to process?",
    "Under the exponential progress we saw recently, a lot of researchers pose the opinion that if an AI system is able to pass the Turing test, the model is not much different to a human mind.",
    "At the very end, if an AI system could persuade us to believe it is \"intelligent\", would it really matter how we define it [33]?"
  ]
}